            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><ab><lb n="1"/>
                <supplied reason="lost">Pro salute et victor</supplied>ia <lb n="2"/><supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>Imp</abbr><ex>eratoris</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>Caes</abbr><ex>aris</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>M</abbr><ex>arci</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>Aur</abbr><ex>eli</ex></expan> Antonini Pii Felicis</supplied> <expan><abbr>Aug</abbr><ex>usti</ex></expan> <lb n="3"/><supplied reason="lost">et Iuliae <expan><abbr>Aug</abbr><ex>ustae</ex></expan> matris Augusti nos</supplied>tri <lb n="4"/><supplied reason="lost">et <expan><abbr>castror</abbr><ex>um</ex></expan> et <expan><abbr>senat</abbr><ex>us</ex></expan> ac patriae</supplied> et <lb n="5"/><supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>imperi</abbr><ex>i</ex></expan> et senatus <expan><abbr>populiq</abbr><ex>ue</ex></expan> Rom</supplied>ani <lb n="6"/><supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>coh</abbr><ex>ors</ex></expan> I |(miliaria) <expan><abbr>Hemes</abbr><ex>enorum</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>Aur</abbr><ex>elia</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>Anton</abbr><ex>iniana</ex></expan> sa</supplied><expan><abbr>g</abbr><ex>ittariorum</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>eq</abbr><ex>uitata</ex></expan>
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Schreibtechnik: litterae aureae (von außen eingedübelt); erhalten sind jedoch nur die Dübellöcher im Stein. Datierung nach Mráv und Visy sehr wahrscheinlich das Jahr 213 n. Chr. Abweichende Rekonstruktion der Zeilen 1 u. 2 durch Visy: geringere Differenz der Buchstabenhöhen, Einfügung einer Widmung an eine Gottheit.</p>
            </div>
